<div class="content-wrap">

  <section class="content-section" aria-labelledby="what-h2">
    <h2 id="what-h2">What is the Ontario CRS Calculator? (OINP Express Entry 2026)</h2>
    <div class="answer-box">
      <strong>Quick Answer:</strong> The Ontario CRS Calculator estimates your federal Comprehensive Ranking System (CRS) score and checks it against OINP's Human Capital Priorities Stream minimum requirement of <strong>400 CRS points</strong> for 2026.
    </div>
    <p>The <strong>Ontario CRS score calculator</strong> uses the official <a href="https://www.ircc.canada.ca/english/immigrate/skilled/crs-tool.asp" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">IRCC Comprehensive Ranking System</a> criteria to estimate your points across four sections: Core Human Capital, Spouse factors, Skill Transferability, and Additional Points. Ontario's OINP then searches the federal Express Entry pool to identify candidates who meet its stream-specific criteria.</p>
    <p>The <strong>OINP Human Capital Priorities Stream</strong> requires a minimum federal CRS of 400, a Bachelor's degree or higher, CLB 7+ in all four language skills, and at least one year of skilled work experience in NOC TEER 0, 1, 2, or 3. [web:180] An Ontario provincial nomination adds <strong>+600 federal CRS points</strong> — near-guaranteeing your next ITA.</p>

    <h3>OINP Score Requirements at a Glance</h3>
    <table class="range-table" aria-label="OINP eligibility thresholds">
      <thead><tr><th>OINP Stream</th><th>Min. CRS / Score</th><th>Key Requirement</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Human Capital Priorities (HCP)</td><td>400 CRS</td><td>Bachelor's+, CLB 7+, 1yr skilled work exp.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>French-Speaking Skilled Worker</td><td>No min CRS</td><td>NCLC 7+ in French, Express Entry eligible</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Skilled Trades</td><td>No min CRS</td><td>Certificate of qualification in trade</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Employer Job Offer: Foreign Worker</td><td>Score 54+</td><td>Valid Ontario employer job offer</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Employer Job Offer: International Student</td><td>Score 63+</td><td>Ontario education + job offer</td></tr>
        <tr><td>In-Demand Skills Stream</td><td>Score varies</td><td>Job offer in 1 of 39 priority occupations</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <p style="margin-top:10px;font-size:0.8rem;color:var(--text-muted);">Source: <a href="https://www.ontario.ca/page/2026-ontario-immigrant-nominee-program-updates" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Ontario.ca OINP 2026 Updates</a>. For reference only.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="content-section" aria-labelledby="how-use-h2">
    <h2 id="how-use-h2">How to Use This Ontario CRS Calculator</h2>
    <div class="steps">
      <div class="step"><div class="step-text"><strong>Enter Personal Details</strong> — Select your age, education level, and marital status. If married/common-law, add your spouse's education and language scores for extra points.</div></div>
      <div class="step"><div class="step-text"><strong>Add Language Scores</strong> — Enter your IELTS or CELPIP scores as CLB levels for all four skills. OINP requires minimum CLB 7 for the HCP stream. Use our <a href="/clb-scores">CLB Score Converter</a> to convert IELTS bands.</div></div>
      <div class="step"><div class="step-text"><strong>Enter Work Experience</strong> — Select years of Canadian work experience. Having 1+ years of Canadian experience in NOC TEER 0/1/2/3 is required for the OINP HCP stream.</div></div>
      <div class="step"><div class="step-text"><strong>Add Ontario-Specific Factors</strong> — Select if you work in Ontario's priority occupations (Healthcare, Technology, Construction, Manufacturing) or if you have a valid Ontario job offer.</div></div>
      <div class="step"><div class="step-text"><strong>View Instant Results</strong> — Get your estimated federal CRS score plus an Ontario OINP eligibility assessment immediately.</div></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content-section" aria-labelledby="breakdown-h2">
    <h2 id="breakdown-h2">How is CRS Score Calculated for Ontario PNP?</h2>
    <div class="answer-box">
      <strong>Quick Answer:</strong> Your federal CRS (max 1,200) is calculated from Age + Education + Language + Canadian Work Experience + Skill Transferability + Additional Points. Ontario then adds +600 upon nomination.
    </div>
    <p>The federal CRS score used for Ontario Express Entry is calculated from the same <a href="https://www.canada.ca/en/immigration-refugees-citizenship/services/immigrate-canada/express-entry/eligibility/criteria-comprehensive-ranking-system/grid.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">IRCC CRS grid</a> as all Express Entry streams. Here's how points are allocated:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Section A — Core Human Capital (500 pts max):</strong> Age (110), Education (150), Language — first official (160), Canadian work experience (80)</li>
      <li><strong>Section B — Spouse/Partner Factors (40 pts max):</strong> Spouse education, language skills, and Canadian work experience</li>
      <li><strong>Section C — Skill Transferability (100 pts max):</strong> Education + language or work experience combinations for bonus points</li>
      <li><strong>Section D — Additional Points (600 pts max):</strong> PNP nomination (+600), valid job offer (+50/+200), Canadian education (+15/+30), French language (+25/+50), sibling in Canada (+15)</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Use our <a href="/">main CRS Calculator</a> for the full breakdown, or <a href="/improve-score">Improve CRS Score guide</a> for the 10 fastest ways to boost points.</p>
  </section>

